03/12/2002
ANKARA, Turkey -- The US government sent a request to Turkey on Monday (2 December) on the use of Turkish military bases and sea ports in a possible military operation against Iraq, according to reports from NTV and Hurriyet. The Turkish government has been asked to respond by 8 December, according to both media outlets. US Deputy Defence Secretary Paul Wolfowitz and Undersecretary of State Marc Grossman are expected to arrive Tuesday to discuss the matter further. (Hurriyet, Anadolu Agency - 03/12/02; NTV - 02/12/02)
